│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash is an assertion in ScalarEvolution::isLoopEntryGuardedByCond that   │
│ checks both LHS and RHS are available at loop entry. This is triggered while  │
│ building VPlan for the second loop (loop.2) after vectorizing the first loop  │
│ (loop.1). The printed SCEV for loop.2's backedge-taken count references a     │
│ value %0 (the load from %p in loop.1) and a composed smax expression,         │
│ indicating that SE has cached an ExitCount for loop.2 that depends on a       │
│ symbol originating in loop.1. After vectorization, the dominance and          │
│ placement of the original %0 change: it's cloned into the vector region, and  │
│ a different scalar load (%4) remains in the scalar remainder, and the LCSSA   │
│ value at exit.1 is updated to be %3 from middle.block. As a result, the       │
│ previously cached SCEV at the scope of loop.2 is no longer valid because it   │
│ relies on a value no longer available at loop.2 entry.                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ - Before vectorization, SCEV prints loop.2 backedge-taken count as (-100 +    │
│ (-1 * %0) + (100 smax (100 + %0))). The %0 is the load i32, ptr %p from       │
│ loop.1.                                                                       │
│ - LoopVectorize processes loop.1, builds and executes VPlan. The final IR     │
│ shows %0 cloned in vector.body and a different load %4 in the scalar part,    │
│ and %add.lcssa getting an extra incoming %3 from middle.block.                │
│ - After vectorizing loop.1, LV proceeds to consider loop.2 and queries SE for │
│ trip count. SE invokes getTripCountFromExitCount and during                   │
│ CanAddOneWithoutOverflow it calls isLoopEntryGuardedByCond(L, ICMP_NE,        │
│ ExitCount, -1). The assert fails on isAvailableAtLoopEntry(LHS), i.e.,        │
│ ExitCount is not available at loop.2 entry due to stale cache.                │
│ - LV already calls PSE.getSE()->forgetLoop(OrigLoop),                         │
│ forgetBlockAndLoopDispositions(), and forgetLcssaPhiWithNewPredecessor for    │
│ exit PHIs of the original loop, but the later SCEV for loop.2 still           │
│ references stale %0.                                                          │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ ScalarEvolution caches backedge/exit counts that may be defined in terms of   │
│ values available at the time of computation. Vectorizing loop.1 changes IR    │
│ such that an SSA value (%0) used in loop.2's cached ExitCount is no longer    │
│ dominating or even present at loop.2 entry. While LV invalidates SE state for │
│ the vectorized loop (forgetLoop(OrigLoop)) and some dispositions, it does not │
│ invalidate SE's cached information for other loops in the function, such as   │
│ loop.2, whose ExitCount depended on a value from the transformed loop. This   │
│ leads to SE reusing a now-invalid ExitCount for loop.2, and the assert in     │
│ isLoopEntryGuardedByCond trips because isAvailableAtLoopEntry(LHS) is false.  │
│                                                                               │
│ Given the assertion is correct, we must invalidate SE's cached information    │
│ that depends on the transformed IR before querying it for other loops.        │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                       │
│ - Location: Inside InnerLoopVectorizer::fixVectorizedLoop, right after the    │
│ existing calls to forgetLoop(OrigLoop) and forgetBlockAndLoopDispositions(),  │
│ add invalidation of SE for all loops in the function so that any cached       │
│ backedge/exit counts (including for loop.2) are recomputed based on the new   │
│ IR.                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit:                                                                         │
│ 2940   // Forget the original basic block.                                    │
│ 2941   PSE.getSE()->forgetLoop(OrigLoop);                                     │
│ 2942   PSE.getSE()->forgetBlockAndLoopDispositions();                         │
│ 2943                                                                          │
│ 2944   // Also forget SCEV information for all other loops in the function,   │
│ because                                                                       │
│ 2945   // vectorizing the current loop may change dominance/availability of   │
│ values                                                                        │
│ 2946   // referenced by cached backedge/exit counts of subsequent loops. This │
│ ensures                                                                       │
│ 2947   // SE will recompute trip/exit counts based on the transformed IR.     │
│ 2948   if (LI) {                                                              │
│ 2949     for (Loop *L : *LI) {                                                │
│ 2950       PSE.getSE()->forgetLoop(L);                                        │
│ 2951     }                                                                    │
│ 2952   }                                                                      │
│ 2953                                                                          │
│ 2954   // After vectorization, the exit blocks of the original loop will have │
│ 2955   // additional predecessors. Invalidate SCEVs for the exit phis in case │
│ SE                                                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ This uses the existing ScalarEvolution::forgetLoop API to conservatively      │
│ invalidate cached information for all loops known to LoopInfo, including      │
│ loop.2. While conservative, it is safe and prevents SE from using stale SCEVs │
│ that reference values no longer available at loop entries after               │
│ transformation.                                                               │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The crash is caused by SE reusing a cached ExitCount for loop.2 that          │
│ references a value (%0) whose availability changed due to vectorizing loop.1. │
│ The fix is to broaden invalidation after vectorization to include all loops   │
│ in the function, not just the vectorized loop, by calling forgetLoop on each  │
│ Loop from LoopInfo. This forces SE to recompute loop.2's backedge/exit counts │
│ based on the updated IR, satisfying isAvailableAtLoopEntry and avoiding the   │
│ assertion. The expected effect is that LV can safely proceed to analyze and   │
│ vectorize loop.2 without hitting the assert, and SCEV prints will reflect     │
│ updated expressions without stale operands.                                   │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
