  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash is an assertion in
ScalarEvolution::isLoopEntryGuardedByCond that checks both LHS and RHS are
available at loop entry. This is triggered while building VPlan for the second
loop (loop.2) after vectorizing the first loop (loop.1). The printed SCEV for
loop.2's backedge-taken count references a value %0 (the load from %p in loop.1)
and a composed smax expression, indicating that SE has cached an ExitCount for
loop.2 that depends on a symbol originating in loop.1. After vectorization, the
dominance and placement of the original %0 change: it's cloned into the vector
region, and a different scalar load (%4) remains in the scalar remainder, and the
LCSSA value at exit.1 is updated to be %3 from middle.block. As a result, the
previously cached SCEV at the scope of loop.2 is no longer valid because it
relies on a value no longer available at loop.2 entry.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's
Log:\n- Before vectorization, SCEV prints loop.2 backedge-taken count as (-100 +
(-1 * %0) + (100 smax (100 + %0))). The %0 is the load i32, ptr %p from
loop.1.\n- LoopVectorize processes loop.1, builds and executes VPlan. The final
IR shows %0 cloned in vector.body and a different load %4 in the scalar part, and
%add.lcssa getting an extra incoming %3 from middle.block.\n- After vectorizing
loop.1, LV proceeds to consider loop.2 and queries SE for trip count. SE invokes
getTripCountFromExitCount and during CanAddOneWithoutOverflow it calls
isLoopEntryGuardedByCond(L, ICMP_NE, ExitCount, -1). The assert fails on
isAvailableAtLoopEntry(LHS), i.e., ExitCount is not available at loop.2 entry due
to stale cache.\n- LV already calls PSE.getSE()->forgetLoop(OrigLoop),
forgetBlockAndLoopDispositions(), and forgetLcssaPhiWithNewPredecessor for exit
PHIs of the original loop, but the later SCEV for loop.2 still references stale
%0.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nScalarEvolution caches backedge/exit counts that
may be defined in terms of values available at the time of computation.
Vectorizing loop.1 changes IR such that an SSA value (%0) used in loop.2's cached
ExitCount is no longer dominating or even present at loop.2 entry. While LV
invalidates SE state for the vectorized loop (forgetLoop(OrigLoop)) and some
dispositions, it does not invalidate SE's cached information for other loops in
the function, such as loop.2, whose ExitCount depended on a value from the
transformed loop. This leads to SE reusing a now-invalid ExitCount for loop.2,
and the assert in isLoopEntryGuardedByCond trips because
isAvailableAtLoopEntry(LHS) is false.\n\nGiven the assertion is correct, we must
invalidate SE's cached information that depends on the transformed IR before
querying it for other loops.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n- File:
llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp\n- Location: Inside
InnerLoopVectorizer::fixVectorizedLoop, right after the existing calls to
forgetLoop(OrigLoop) and forgetBlockAndLoopDispositions(), add invalidation of SE
for all loops in the function so that any cached backedge/exit counts (including
for loop.2) are recomputed based on the new IR.\n\nEdit:\n2940   // Forget the
original basic block.\n2941   PSE.getSE()->forgetLoop(OrigLoop);\n2942
