PSE.getSE()->forgetLoop(L);\n2951     }\n2952   }\n2953 \n2954   // After
vectorization, the exit blocks of the original loop will have\n2955   //
additional predecessors. Invalidate SCEVs for the exit phis in case SE\n\nThis
uses the existing ScalarEvolution::forgetLoop API to conservatively invalidate
cached information for all loops known to LoopInfo, including loop.2. While
conservative, it is safe and prevents SE from using stale SCEVs that reference
values no longer available at loop entries after transformation.\n\n5.
Conclusion:\nThe crash is caused by SE reusing a cached ExitCount for loop.2 that
references a value (%0) whose availability changed due to vectorizing loop.1. The
fix is to broaden invalidation after vectorization to include all loops in the
